The paper focuses on designing rating systems for online platforms, which involves aspects of human-computer interaction (HC) and information retrieval (IR) to ensure that the ratings are informative. The study also involves simulations and optimization, which could fall under social and information networks (SI) or cybernetics (CY). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of ratings in online labor markets, which could be classified under electronic commerce (EC).
